olitical entanglements, as well as a long history of global interactions.With contributions by leading anthropologists, sociologists, and political scientists, this volume brings new theoretical approaches into conversation with detailed empirical case studies grounded in modern Asia. In doing so, it offers a fresh and critical analysis of the ways in which political theology is imagined, materialised, and contested both within and beyond nation-states.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical theologyzAsiavCase studies. 0aPolitical theologyzAsia. 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh  aAnthropology.  aAsia.  aDevelopment.  aGovernance.  aHistory.  aModernity.  aPolitical theology.  aPolitics.  aReligion.  aSociology.1 aBolotta, Giuseppe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBolotta, Giuseppe, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aElinoff, Eli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeener, R. Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeener, R. Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFountain, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFountain, Philip, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGeorge, Kenneth M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHan, Sam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKale, Sunila S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMostowlansky, Till, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNovetzke, Christian Lee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalvatore, Armando, econtributor